Directly after the release of their first album Enter, the band became prominent 
in the underground scene. It would however take until 2001, when they became known 
by the general public, with the single "Ice Queen" from the album Mother Earth, 
which reached #2 on the charts. Since then, the band won the Conamus Exportprijs
five years in a row. Their next album The Silent Force debuted at #1 on the 
Dutch charts. Their latest album, The Heart of Everything, also debuted at #1.
